02:16.500 --> 02:18.500
- Please welcome comedian

02:18.500 --> 02:21.969
and sleight-of-hand
artist Erik Tait.

02:21.969 --> 02:24.000
- Hello!

02:24.000 --> 02:28.000
[cheers and applause]

02:28.000 --> 02:32.069
- Hello, everybody,
I am terrified to be here.

02:32.069 --> 02:33.569
This is--
oh, man, this is great.

02:33.569 --> 02:36.030
Uh, everyone, please join me
in giving a giant round

02:36.030 --> 02:37.670
of peer pressure
to Alyson Hannigan

02:37.670 --> 02:38.969
as she joins me at the table.

02:38.969 --> 02:40.569
- [laughs]

02:40.569 --> 02:42.829
- So nice to meet you.
- Nice to see you.

02:42.829 --> 02:45.599
- Sit right there for me.
This is great.

02:45.599 --> 02:47.199
- Oh.
- So, tonight,

02:47.199 --> 02:48.629
I'm going to teach you
how to steal money.

02:48.629 --> 02:50.469
Specifically, from those two.
Are you on board?

02:50.469 --> 02:52.170
- Sure.
- Dope.

02:52.170 --> 02:54.199
We're going to do that
by playing a little game.

02:54.199 --> 02:55.930
Have you ever played
Three-card Monte before?

02:55.930 --> 02:57.370
- Uh, no.

02:57.370 --> 02:58.699
- It's a brilliant game,
tremendous.

02:58.699 --> 03:00.830
You're going to love it.
It uses two black sevens.

03:00.830 --> 03:03.330
- Mm-hmm.
- And a red queen.

03:03.330 --> 03:04.669
- Okay.

03:04.669 --> 03:06.800
- The idea is that the cards
go face down,

03:06.800 --> 03:09.270
then they get mixed up,
and then people bet money

03:09.270 --> 03:11.669
to figure out if they can see
which one is the queen.

03:11.669 --> 03:13.300
Actually, were you following?
- Yes.

03:13.300 --> 03:14.599
- Which one is the queen?
- The middle one.

03:14.599 --> 03:16.199
- The middle one.

03:16.199 --> 03:17.500
- Ha.
- That was an excellent guess.

03:17.500 --> 03:18.770
You're a natural.
- Well, you were slow.

03:18.770 --> 03:19.829
So thanks.

03:19.829 --> 03:21.129
[laughter]

03:21.129 --> 03:22.270
- So the trouble
with this "game"

03:22.270 --> 03:23.500
is that I keep
saying it in quotes,

03:23.500 --> 03:25.400
because it's actually
more of a scam or a con.

03:25.400 --> 03:27.099
Like an M. Night
Shyamalan movie.

03:27.099 --> 03:29.000
[laughter]

03:29.000 --> 03:30.969
Magicians have studied
this game for years,

03:30.969 --> 03:32.629
so they understand all
of the little fiddly bits

03:32.629 --> 03:35.569
that transform it from a simple
game into a crime.

03:35.569 --> 03:37.829
So if you wanted to use this
to rip off magicians

03:37.829 --> 03:39.969
like Penn and Teller, you would
play Three-card Monte,

03:39.969 --> 03:41.329
but you would play it...

03:41.329 --> 03:43.199
[cards slapping down]

03:43.199 --> 03:44.370
with invisible cards.

03:44.370 --> 03:46.599
[audience gasps]

03:46.599 --> 03:48.770
- So, Alyson, you've got
two black sevens.

03:48.770 --> 03:50.400
- Uh-huh, okay.

03:50.400 --> 03:51.699
[laughter]

03:51.699 --> 03:53.300
Yeah.
- Are you okay?

03:53.300 --> 03:54.599
- Yeah.
- All right.

03:54.599 --> 03:56.129
You got a red queen.
- Mm.

03:56.129 --> 03:58.129
- You mix them up...

03:58.129 --> 03:59.170
and you are never
going to learn anything

03:59.170 --> 04:00.370
if I do it all for you.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.500
Get in there
and mix up those cards.

04:01.500 --> 04:02.500
- [laughs]

04:02.500 --> 04:03.870
Okay.
- Yeah.

04:03.870 --> 04:05.199
- [whooshing noises]

04:05.199 --> 04:06.569
[audience laughs]

04:06.569 --> 04:09.629
- I did the sound effects
so it felt like it was real.

04:09.629 --> 04:10.699
[audience laughs]

04:10.699 --> 04:12.569
- That was totes perf.

04:12.569 --> 04:13.599
[laughter]

04:13.599 --> 04:14.830
- Okay.

04:14.830 --> 04:16.430
- So, Alyson,
what I'd like you to do now,

04:16.430 --> 04:19.370
bet the boys $20
they can't find the queen.

04:19.370 --> 04:21.129
- Hey, guys.

04:21.129 --> 04:25.329
Um, I bet you 20 of his dollars
that you can't find the queen.

04:25.329 --> 04:26.800
- Do you not have $20?

04:26.800 --> 04:29.000
- [stammers]

04:29.000 --> 04:31.129
It's not on me.
- That's okay, I came prepared.

04:31.129 --> 04:32.269
- Aw, thanks.

04:32.269 --> 04:33.430
- I'll bankroll you
for round one.

04:33.430 --> 04:34.529
- Okay.
- So here's the deal.

04:34.529 --> 04:35.769
Penn and Teller are going to

04:35.769 --> 04:37.100
have to make a decision
in just a moment.

04:37.100 --> 04:38.500
What I'd like you to do
is take this bill

04:38.500 --> 04:40.029
and whenever
they make the decision,

04:40.029 --> 04:42.899
place it wherever they say,
in position one, two, or three.

04:42.899 --> 04:44.129
Go ahead and take the bill.

04:44.129 --> 04:45.569
- Okay.
- Excellent.

04:45.569 --> 04:47.930
Penn, Teller,
which one's the queen?

04:47.930 --> 04:49.399
- The middle one.
- Middle one?

04:49.399 --> 04:50.899
- All right.
- Go ahead and place it down.

04:50.899 --> 04:52.329
- [whooshing sound]
- Yeah, nice job.

04:52.329 --> 04:55.269
- It's still the sound effects.
- Yeah.

04:55.269 --> 04:57.199
- They are correct.

04:57.199 --> 04:59.600
- Wow.
- That's an excellent guess.

04:59.600 --> 05:02.529
[laughter]

05:02.529 --> 05:05.529
- So who gets the 20?
- Well, you just lost me $20.

05:05.529 --> 05:08.569
- Oh, sorry, I do that.
- It's okay, don't worry.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.199
Everything is going
according to plan, right?

05:10.199 --> 05:12.129
What you just did is called
"setting the hook."

05:12.129 --> 05:13.370
- Oh.
- They won a little bit

05:13.370 --> 05:14.470
of money, now,
they're going to want to win

05:14.470 --> 05:15.670
a little bit more, right?

05:15.670 --> 05:17.329
So for round two,
all we're going to do

05:17.329 --> 05:19.000
is switch the two black sevens.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.129
Go ahead, get in there and
switch the two black sevens.

05:21.129 --> 05:22.269
- [whooshing sound]

05:22.269 --> 05:23.600
- You are crushing this!

05:23.600 --> 05:25.269
[laughter]

05:25.269 --> 05:27.230
- All right, Alyson, this time,
raise the stakes a bit.

05:27.230 --> 05:29.670
Bet them $50
they can't find the queen.

05:29.670 --> 05:34.329
- Guys, $50 of his money
that you can't find the queen.

05:34.329 --> 05:35.899
- I'm going to go ahead and--
- Ooh.

05:35.899 --> 05:37.399
- Yeah, I'll stay the course
here for round two, sound good?

05:37.399 --> 05:39.629
- All right, sounds good to me.
- Same deal as before.

05:39.629 --> 05:41.870
They have to make a decision,
position one, two, or three.

05:41.870 --> 05:43.699
Wherever they say,
please place the bill.

05:43.699 --> 05:46.430
Penn, Teller--
- [whooshing sound]

05:46.430 --> 05:47.769
- Which card
should be the queen?

05:47.769 --> 05:50.769
- Well, uh, I think
it's the one on the left.

05:50.769 --> 05:52.529
Uh, his left.
- My left?

05:52.529 --> 05:53.870
- The Irish left.
- Over there?

05:53.870 --> 05:55.000
- Yeah, yeah, right there.
- Okay.

05:55.000 --> 05:56.399
- Got you.

05:56.399 --> 05:58.769
Now, a lot of people were
rooting for the first one.

05:58.769 --> 06:00.399
A lot of people here thought
it was in the center.

06:00.399 --> 06:02.230
I know some people
may have thought it was.

06:02.230 --> 06:04.769
But it's not the queen,
it's a black seven.

06:04.769 --> 06:07.370
Unfortunately for Penn,
he placed the bet here.

06:07.370 --> 06:09.569
You would have
placed the bet here.

06:09.569 --> 06:11.769
Because that
is where the queen is.

06:11.769 --> 06:13.870
- Oh!

06:13.870 --> 06:16.930
[applause]

06:23.170 --> 06:25.230
- Penn, I know you would have
preferred this outcome,

06:25.230 --> 06:26.970
but in each life,
a little rain must fall.

06:26.970 --> 06:28.470
- Exactly.

06:28.470 --> 06:29.699
- I have good news.
- Yeah?

06:29.699 --> 06:31.829
- Good news, right,
we're up to 30 bucks.

06:31.829 --> 06:32.970
- That's great.
- And they're mad at you

06:32.970 --> 06:35.000
because you cheated them.
- Oh, sorry guys.

06:35.000 --> 06:36.230
- We're going to go
for round three now,

06:36.230 --> 06:37.769
but we're going to do it
a little bit differently.

06:37.769 --> 06:39.730
We're going to take the third
card, and put it right there.

06:39.730 --> 06:42.170
Right, but when you do so, you
put it down very aggressively,

06:42.170 --> 06:43.730
so that it ends up
with a bend in the corner.

06:43.730 --> 06:45.699
I'm not going to say anything.
Just let them see it.

06:45.699 --> 06:47.000
The pros call this
"throwing a lug."

06:47.000 --> 06:48.670
You turn
the other card face down,

06:48.670 --> 06:49.930
there's only two moves left.

06:49.930 --> 06:52.230
And I'm going
to make them for you, okay?

06:52.230 --> 06:55.230
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:55.230 --> 06:59.699
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:59.699 --> 07:01.329
- Very high-end
sleight of hand.

07:01.329 --> 07:02.569
- Hm.

07:02.569 --> 07:03.829
- And we're going to go
for all the cash.

07:03.829 --> 07:05.500
- Oh, boy.
- Bet them $100

07:05.500 --> 07:07.670
they can't find the queen.

07:07.670 --> 07:11.769
- He says he has $100
to bet you guys for the queen.

07:11.769 --> 07:13.899
- I'm on.
- Whoo.

07:13.899 --> 07:16.600
- I'm out.
- Oh, he doesn't have it.

07:16.600 --> 07:17.800
- Are you sure you don't have

07:17.800 --> 07:19.029
any of that "Buffy" money
laying around?

07:19.029 --> 07:20.199
- [groans]

07:20.199 --> 07:22.069
[audience laughs]

07:22.069 --> 07:23.629
- It's okay,
we'll go to my stash.

07:23.629 --> 07:25.529
- Okay.

07:25.529 --> 07:29.600
[laughter]

07:29.600 --> 07:31.170
- My beard.
- That's handy in Vegas.

07:31.170 --> 07:34.529
- Yeah, it is.
- Yeah.

07:34.529 --> 07:38.870
- 20, 40, 60, 80, 100 dollars.

07:38.870 --> 07:40.569
- Whoo!
- Yeah.

07:40.569 --> 07:42.129
- Big spender.
- This time,

07:42.129 --> 07:43.870
uh, don't bother placing the
cash on any of the cards.

07:43.870 --> 07:45.529
Just keep an eye on them,
because we might have to run.

07:45.529 --> 07:47.000
- Okay.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.970
- While Penn and Teller
were focused on the cash there,

07:48.970 --> 07:50.500
Alyson got in,
and she switched it,

07:50.500 --> 07:52.029
so now the queen
is sitting right here

07:52.029 --> 07:53.470
next to my left hand.

07:53.470 --> 07:55.170
Stellar work, Alyson.
Nice job.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.529
[audience laughs]

07:56.529 --> 08:00.470
Penn, Teller, last round.
Which one is the queen?

08:00.470 --> 08:02.000
- [exhales]

08:02.000 --> 08:04.300
I would say
the one on your right.

08:04.300 --> 08:06.300
- That corner works every time.

08:06.300 --> 08:08.629
Gentleman, that right there
is the red queen.

08:08.629 --> 08:09.829
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

08:09.829 --> 08:11.000
- Oh!

08:11.000 --> 08:12.129
- These are the
two black sevens.

08:12.129 --> 08:13.500
- Wow.

08:13.500 --> 08:15.699
- And that's the invisible
Three-card Monte.

08:15.699 --> 08:20.029
[cheers and applause]

08:20.029 --> 08:22.300
- Very, very cool.

08:22.300 --> 08:24.199
Erik Tait,
ladies and gentleman!

08:24.199 --> 08:26.569
- Thank you.
- Come on over.

08:26.569 --> 08:28.529
Wow.
- Nice to meet you.

08:28.529 --> 08:30.000
- That's fantastic.

08:30.000 --> 08:32.669
What are people...
think when they meet you?

08:32.669 --> 08:33.970
Like, what do they
think you do?

08:33.970 --> 08:35.070
- Some people
think I'm a comedian.

08:35.070 --> 08:36.730
Other people think
I'm a magician.

08:36.730 --> 08:39.870
Uh, I'm just happy when they
hire me and their checks clear.

08:39.870 --> 08:42.029
So, that's--that's it.

08:42.029 --> 08:43.669
- And you're
a comedy writer as well.

08:43.669 --> 08:45.570
- Yeah, comedy and magic
are kind of weird, though,

08:45.570 --> 08:47.570
because comedy, uh--I think
there's a great magician

08:47.570 --> 08:49.070
who said something about how

08:49.070 --> 08:51.100
comedy is fundamentally
about telling a truth,

08:51.100 --> 08:52.230
and magic
is about fundamentally

08:52.230 --> 08:53.470
about telling a lie.

08:53.470 --> 08:55.669
And so, they don't really
work well together.

08:55.669 --> 08:58.470
So it's really a delicate
balance to try and figure out,

08:58.470 --> 09:00.629
you know, how to make things
funny and magical.

09:00.629 --> 09:03.029
- Yeah, well, I think you've
done a really good job at that.

09:03.029 --> 09:04.730
- Oh, thank you very much.
- All right.

09:04.730 --> 09:06.200
Well, let's see
what Penn and Teller thought.

09:06.200 --> 09:08.700
- Okie doke.
- Penn, Teller.

09:08.700 --> 09:10.299
- You know,
you're really funny,

09:10.299 --> 09:11.870
and it's a
really different style.

09:11.870 --> 09:14.470
It's a really nice, different
style, seeing that, uh,

09:14.470 --> 09:17.870
you know, taking a gambling
thing, the premise,

09:17.870 --> 09:19.200
and just taking it
to another place.

09:19.200 --> 09:22.669
I loved you pulling the, uh,
money out of your beard.

09:22.669 --> 09:23.870
Wicked good.

09:23.870 --> 09:26.129
What's the use
of having an ironic beard

09:26.129 --> 09:27.299
if you can't have an ironic

09:27.299 --> 09:28.730
magic trick to go with it,
right?

09:28.730 --> 09:32.029
And uh, the choreography
is just perfect.

09:32.029 --> 09:35.830
All the--all the moves
are just clean and wonderful,

09:35.830 --> 09:38.899
and timed perfectly, nothing's
even slightly awkward.

09:38.899 --> 09:41.070
But I want to do kind of
a non-sequitur here.

09:41.070 --> 09:43.100
You seem very healthy.

09:43.100 --> 09:44.870
Are you a healthy guy?

09:44.870 --> 09:47.799
- Yeah, I--I--I've been
to a gym once or...thrice.

09:47.799 --> 09:48.899
- Any, uh--

09:48.899 --> 09:50.330
Any medical work done?

09:50.330 --> 09:52.169
Like, I wondering if maybe
Doctor Leonard Green

09:52.169 --> 09:55.429
gave any laparoscopic surgery,
any of that going?

09:55.429 --> 09:57.769
- Oh, yeah, I'm
laterally aware of the idea

09:57.769 --> 09:58.830
that you're
trying to snap out there.

09:58.830 --> 10:01.470
[laughter]

10:01.470 --> 10:03.070
- Does that mean he got you?

10:03.070 --> 10:05.200
- A lot of times,
we talk in code.

10:05.200 --> 10:07.500
It's not often people
talk back to us in code.

10:07.500 --> 10:10.399
That's really great.
That's really great.

10:10.399 --> 10:14.100
You--you get an idea of the 411
I'm laying on you there?

10:14.100 --> 10:16.129
- Yeah, oh, yeah, uh, I'm done.

10:16.129 --> 10:17.769
[laughter]

10:17.769 --> 10:19.330
- So clearly, they know,

10:19.330 --> 10:21.570
and you made Penn
laugh very loudly.

10:21.570 --> 10:23.500
- That's really all I wanted.
- Awesome.

10:23.500 --> 10:25.570
Thank you so much.
Erik Tait, everyone!

10:25.570 --> 10:26.830
- Thanks so much.

10:26.830 --> 10:30.230
[cheers and applause]

10:32.000 --> 10:33.399
- We got to take a break,

10:33.399 --> 10:35.200
but we have
more foolers on the way.

10:35.200 --> 10:39.129
Including our two favorite
fools, Penn and Teller!

10:39.129 --> 10:40.299
Stick around.

10:40.299 --> 10:43.299
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

10:43.299 --> 10:44.870
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:47.729 --> 10:50.729
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

10:50.729 --> 10:51.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:51.970 --> 10:54.930
- Welcome back.
I'm no mind reader,

10:54.930 --> 10:57.700
but I get a sense you're going
to love our next act.

10:57.700 --> 10:58.800
Let's meet her.

10:58.800 --> 11:00.899
<i>[bright musical flourish]</i>

11:00.899 --> 11:03.029
<i>- I think it's quite tough
to be a woman in magic.</i>

11:03.029 --> 11:06.999
People expect you
to be the sidekick.

11:06.999 --> 11:09.629
<i>It's really important
to be strong.</i>

11:09.629 --> 11:13.529
I had a friend at university
who did magic.

11:13.529 --> 11:16.470
<i>She would ask for a volunteer
from the audience,</i>

11:16.470 --> 11:18.029
<i>and I would raise my hand.</i>

11:18.029 --> 11:20.229
<i>She would
guess my number right.</i>

11:20.229 --> 11:21.830
Yes, it is!

11:21.830 --> 11:23.999
But really, she knew what the
number was the whole time.

11:23.999 --> 11:26.629
<i>I found that there was this
kind of power you felt</i>

11:26.629 --> 11:27.800
<i>being on the stage.</i>

11:27.800 --> 11:30.070
<i>And I felt like I wanted to be</i>

11:30.070 --> 11:31.899
<i>kind of more
in control of that.</i>

11:31.899 --> 11:33.899
When I started doing
my own mentalism,

11:33.899 --> 11:36.899
I think I did feel like
I had capabilities

11:36.899 --> 11:39.029
<i>that I wasn't aware
that I had before.</i>

11:39.029 --> 11:40.399
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

11:40.399 --> 11:41.899
<i>A big part of my act today</i>

11:41.899 --> 11:45.100
is showing everybody how much
potential they have.

11:45.100 --> 11:47.700
<i>I want them to go away
feeling inspired.</i>

11:47.700 --> 11:50.700
[cheers and applause]

11:52.369 --> 11:54.700
- Please welcome
Rebecca Herrera!

11:58.029 --> 12:00.300
- Now, ladies and gentleman,

12:00.300 --> 12:03.029
I have a secret
I'd like to share with you.

12:03.029 --> 12:06.300
I am able to see with my ears.

12:06.300 --> 12:08.430
I know that sounds strange,
but basically,

12:08.430 --> 12:10.430
this is the ability
to listen to the sound

12:10.430 --> 12:11.970
of a pen on paper

12:11.970 --> 12:15.100
and translate those sounds
into images in your mind.

12:15.100 --> 12:16.470
After years of practice,

12:16.470 --> 12:19.529
I can do this with
quite complex pictures.

12:19.529 --> 12:22.369
But I had to start somewhere
quite simple.

12:22.369 --> 12:23.970
I'd like to show you
where I started,

12:23.970 --> 12:27.100
and maybe you can join in, too.

12:27.100 --> 12:29.970
So I started by drawing
a simple circle.

12:32.800 --> 12:35.700
So you may have noticed
that as I drew the circle,

12:35.700 --> 12:38.170
you could also hear me draw it.

12:38.170 --> 12:39.930
So now, I'd like
to try that again,

12:39.930 --> 12:42.430
but this time, I want you all
to close your eyes,

12:42.430 --> 12:45.369
and listen carefully
as I draw a different shape.

12:45.369 --> 12:47.369
Here we go.

12:51.700 --> 12:53.899
Okay, open your eyes.

12:53.899 --> 12:55.930
If you saw a square
appear in your mind's eye,

12:55.930 --> 12:58.200
please raise your hand.

12:58.200 --> 13:01.100
Yay, that's quite a lot of you.
Amazing.

13:01.100 --> 13:03.729
Okay, so this is
quite a basic test

13:03.729 --> 13:05.430
for seeing with your ears.

13:05.430 --> 13:07.629
But now...

13:07.629 --> 13:11.170
I'd like to take this
one step further.

13:11.170 --> 13:13.899
Teller, would you mind please
joining me on the stage?

13:13.899 --> 13:15.070
Thank you so much.

13:15.070 --> 13:18.070
[applause]

13:20.529 --> 13:23.029
Now, in just a moment,
I'm going to ask you

13:23.029 --> 13:24.470
to draw something on the board,

13:24.470 --> 13:26.499
but first, I'd like you
to make a few checks.

13:26.499 --> 13:28.070
Please check my ears.

13:28.070 --> 13:30.899
Make sure there's nothing
sticking out of them.

13:30.899 --> 13:32.970
Nothing behind them.

13:37.899 --> 13:39.129
Also check my eyes,

13:39.129 --> 13:42.170
make sure there's no
Google contact lenses.

13:42.170 --> 13:43.499
Happy?

13:43.499 --> 13:45.200
You can check my hair as well,
if you like.

13:45.200 --> 13:47.330
Make sure there's nothing
concealed in there.

13:47.330 --> 13:49.269
[giggles]

13:49.269 --> 13:51.229
[laughter]

13:51.229 --> 13:53.930
Now, I'd also like you to
please check this blindfold.

13:53.930 --> 13:55.129
I'd like you to please check

13:55.129 --> 13:56.670
that there's nothing
concealed inside it,

13:56.670 --> 13:59.629
that it's completely opaque,
and there's no hidden pinholes.

14:08.729 --> 14:11.100
Yeah, good?
Wonderful.

14:11.100 --> 14:13.330
Now, would you mind
please helping me

14:13.330 --> 14:15.330
tie this around my eyes?

14:15.330 --> 14:17.529
Make sure it's nice and tight.

14:21.830 --> 14:23.269
Lovely, thank you so much.

14:23.269 --> 14:25.869
So now, I'd like you to
draw something on the board.

14:25.869 --> 14:28.330
Um, please make sure
it's nothing too simple,

14:28.330 --> 14:31.729
like a shape, nothing too
obvious, like a flower,

14:31.729 --> 14:36.129
and nothing too complicated,
like a Mona Lisa, or a Picasso.

14:36.129 --> 14:38.629
Um, but something
that you could draw in say,

14:38.629 --> 14:42.529
10 to 15 seconds, and that
everyone here will recognize.

14:42.529 --> 14:44.100
Once you've finished
your drawing,

14:44.100 --> 14:46.670
please recap the pen,
place it in my hand,

14:46.670 --> 14:48.899
and then stand
to the side of the board.

14:48.899 --> 14:51.269
You may begin your drawing now.

15:11.499 --> 15:14.300
Okay, so I'm just...

15:14.300 --> 15:18.129
